 BARBERTON –According to Capt Jabu Ndubane, Barberton police spokesman, three suspects entered the CRF Metal building at around 08:00 on Monday. Read More: EFF MP robbed at home They told Craffet that they wanted to hire his transport to go and collect scrap metal in Emjindini Trust. While Craffet was busy arranging for the transport they produce a firearm and force him to the office. They assaulted him with their fists in the chest and demanded cash,” said Ndubane. The suspects took R10 000 in cash and fled the scene on foot. Also Read:Car break-in caught on camera Ndubane said Local Criminal Record Centre Unit was called to the scene. “No arrest has been made yet. But investigations are continuing,” said Ndubane.